api_list.name: Get Accounts
api_list.description:
### Retrieve File Content:

**Method:** GET
**URL:** https://api-url.com/api/files/{filename}
**Description:** Retrieves the content of the specified file.
### Usage Instructions:

**Endpoint:** https://api-url.com/api/files/{filename}
**Parameters:**
{filename}: The name of the file whose content you want to retrieve.
**Response:** The content of the specified file.

**NOTE:** Testing this with the Rapid Api Play ground will not work to avoid abuse
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://freeaccountsapi.p.rapidapi.com/files/fullfileName"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "freeaccountsapi.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

api_list.description:
### List Available Files:

**Method:** GET
**URL:** https://api-url.com/api/files
**Description:** Returns a list of available files.

### Usage Instructions:

Endpoint: https://api-url.com/api/files
Response: A JSON array containing the names of available files.
